# Procurement Order Workflow Review & Testing Prompt

## Overview

This specialized prompt enables comprehensive review and testing of the 01900 Create Procurement Order workflow, focusing on data collection integrity, agent coordination, document generation accuracy, and logistics integration. Use this prompt for validating the complete procurement order lifecycle from user input through document generation and logistics processing.

## Review Scope

### Primary Review Areas

#### 1. Data Collection System (43 Cards)
The procurement order workflow collects data through 43 interactive cards covering various data points. Review must validate:

- **Card Presentation Consistency**: Verify all 43 cards follow a consistent UI pattern with individual card-based selection
- **Data Point Coverage**: Ensure all required procurement data points are captured across the card collection:
  - Group, Category, Item, and Goods specifications
  - Technical specifications and requirements
  - Quantity and unit of measure
  - Delivery requirements and timelines
  - Budget and cost information
  - Supplier preferences and qualifications
  - Compliance and regulatory requirements
  - Safety and environmental considerations
- **Selection Logic**: Validate card selection mechanisms (single/multi-select) work correctly
- **Data Persistence**: Verify selected card data persists correctly through the workflow
- **Validation Rules**: Confirm proper validation at card level and across card combinations
- **Autofill Function**: Test the autofill function that provides mock data for testing order creation

#### 2. Document Generation System
Validate that user selections correctly populate generated documents:

**Scope of Work (SOW) Generation:**
- Verify SOW sections populate from card selections
- Validate template selection based on order type and complexity
- Confirm technical specifications transfer correctly
- Check that requirements and constraints are properly documented

**Appendices A-F Generation:**
- **Appendix A - Product Specifications**: Validate technical specs, quality standards, packaging requirements
- **Appendix B - Safety Data Sheets**: Verify SDS 16-section compliance, hazard identification, PPE requirements
- **Appendix C - Delivery Schedule**: Confirm timeline data populates correctly, validate Gantt chart data generation
- **Appendix D - Training Materials**: Verify equipment/material training requirements are captured
- **Appendix E - Logistics Documents**: Check transport and documentation requirements
- **Appendix F - Packing/Marking Specifications**: Validate packaging standards and labeling requirements

**Procurement Order Document:**
- Verify order header information (PO/WO/SO numbers)
- Validate line items match card selections
- Confirm pricing and budget alignment
- Check approval routing configuration
- Verify supplier information completeness

#### 3. Agent Wiring & Coordination
Review the agent orchestration system for proper wiring:

**Agent Assignment:**
- Validate agents are correctly assigned based on discipline requirements
- Verify capability matching for document processing tasks
- Confirm workload balancing across available agents
- Check agent status monitoring and real-time updates

**Agent Communication:**
- Verify inter-agent messaging for multi-discipline workflows
- Validate context passing between agents (Group/Category/Item/Goods specs)
- Confirm error handling and fallback mechanisms
- Check agent completion notifications and status updates

**Agent Prompts:**
- Review agent-specific prompts stored in the prompts management system
- Validate prompt retrieval for each agent type
- Confirm prompt versioning and performance tracking
- Test A/B testing integration for prompt optimization

#### 4. Context Usage (Deep-Agents with MD Docs)
Validate proper context management using markdown documentation:

**Context Transfer:**
- Verify order details (Group, Category, Item, Goods) are properly transferred as context
- Validate technical specifications are maintained across agent handoffs
- Confirm supplier requirements persist through workflow stages
- Check that compliance requirements are accessible to all relevant agents

**MD Document Integration:**
- Review how markdown docs transfer context between workflow stages
- Validate PARA navigation paths are correctly referenced
- Confirm gigabrain tags are properly used for knowledge discovery
- Check cross-referencing between related documents

**Context Preservation:**
- Verify context survives HITL handoffs
- Validate context is maintained during parallel processing
- Confirm context integrity across document compilation
- Check context accessibility for audit trails

#### 5. Logistics Workflow Integration (01700 Logistics)
Review the handoff to logistics discipline:

**Logistics Document Generation:**
- Validate automatic export/import document generation for international shipments
- Verify customs data preparation for CDC submission
- Confirm transport documentation completeness
- Check compliance with international shipping regulations

**Logistics Agent Coordination:**
- Review agent handoff from procurement (01900) to logistics (01700)
- Validate context transfer includes all required order details
- Confirm logistics agent receives complete specifications
- Check status synchronization between disciplines

**CDC Submission:**
- Validate customs data preparation accuracy
- Verify regulatory compliance for international shipments
- Confirm submission workflow triggers correctly
- Check audit trail for customs documentation

## Review Execution Framework

### Step 1: Data Collection Validation
```
Using the Construct AI memory system with Gigabrain for 01900 Procurement discipline:

**PARA Navigation:**
- Access docs_construct_ai/para/pages/disciplines/01900_procurement/
- Reference order creation workflow: docs_construct_ai/disciplines/01900_procurement/workflow_docs/
- Check UI implementation: client/src/pages/01900-procurement/

**Gigabrain Search:**
- Search gigabrain tags for "disciplines, 01900_procurement", "order-creation", "data-collection"
- Filter by tags: "card-selection", "ui-consistency", "validation-rules"

**Review Checklist:**
- [ ] All 43 cards render with consistent UI (card-based selection pattern)
- [ ] Card selection logic works correctly (single/multi-select as appropriate)
- [ ] Data validation occurs at card level and across card combinations
- [ ] Selected data persists correctly through workflow stages
- [ ] Autofill function populates mock data for testing
- [ ] Group/Category/Item/Goods hierarchy is properly structured
- [ ] Technical specifications capture all required fields
- [ ] Budget and cost data validates against thresholds
- [ ] Supplier qualification requirements are enforced
- [ ] Compliance and regulatory flags are properly set
```

