## Testing Scenarios

### Scenario 1: Simple Procurement Order (Office Supplies)
```
Test Data (Autofill):
- Group: Office Supplies
- Category: Stationery
- Item: Paper Products
- Goods: A4 Copy Paper (80gsm)
- Quantity: 100 reams
- Budget: $2,500

Expected Outcomes:
- [ ] 43 cards present with consistent UI
- [ ] Basic cards selected (no complex technical specs needed)
- [ ] SOW generates with standard template
- [ ] Appendices A and C generated (basic specs and delivery)
- [ ] Agent assignment: Procurement only (01900)
- [ ] Context transfer: Basic order details
- [ ] No logistics workflow triggered (domestic delivery)
```

### Scenario 2: Complex Equipment Procurement
```
Test Data (Autofill):
- Group: Heavy Equipment
- Category: Earthmoving
- Item: Excavator
- Goods: CAT 320 Excavator with attachments
- Specifications: Technical specs, safety requirements, training needs
- Budget: $250,000
- International: Yes (customs required)

Expected Outcomes:
- [ ] All 43 cards available with complex technical options
- [ ] Multiple cards selected across categories
- [ ] SOW generates with technical template
- [ ] All appendices A-F generated
- [ ] Agent assignment: Multi-discipline (01900, 00800-00872, 02400, 01700)
- [ ] Context transfer: Complete technical specifications
- [ ] Logistics workflow triggered (international shipment)
- [ ] CDC submission prepared
```

### Scenario 3: Service Order with Training Requirements
```
Test Data (Autofill):
- Group: Professional Services
- Category: Technical Consulting
- Item: Equipment Training
- Goods: Crane Operation Certification
- Duration: 2 weeks
- Budget: $15,000
- Compliance: Safety certification required

Expected Outcomes:
- [ ] Service-specific cards selected
- [ ] Training requirements captured in cards
- [ ] SOW generates with service template
- [ ] Appendices A, B, D generated (specs, safety, training)
- [ ] Agent assignment: Procurement, Safety, HR (01900, 02400, 01500)
- [ ] Context transfer: Training specifications
- [ ] HITL task for safety compliance review
```

## Issue Identification Framework

### Data Collection Issues
```
Common Issues:
- Inconsistent card UI rendering
- Missing validation on card selections
- Data not persisting across workflow stages
- Autofill function not working
- Group/Category/Item/Goods hierarchy broken

Resolution Approach:
- Review card component implementation
- Check validation logic in order creation service
- Verify data persistence in database schema
- Test autofill function with mock data
- Validate hierarchy relationships in data model
```

### Document Generation Issues
```
Common Issues:
- SOW sections not populating from cards
- Appendix content incomplete or incorrect
- Template selection not matching order type
- Document compilation failing

Resolution Approach:
- Review SOW generation service logic
- Check appendix-specific generation functions
- Validate template selection algorithm
- Test document compilation pipeline
```

### Agent Wiring Issues
```
Common Issues:
- Agents not assigned to correct disciplines
- Capability matching failing
- Context not passing between agents
- Agent prompts not retrieving correctly

Resolution Approach:
- Review discipline assignment logic
- Check capability assessment algorithms
- Validate context transfer mechanisms
- Test agent prompt retrieval from management system
```

### Context Transfer Issues
```
Common Issues:
- Order details lost during handoffs
- Technical specs not maintained
- Compliance requirements not accessible
- MD docs not referencing context correctly

Resolution Approach:
- Review context management service
- Check data serialization for handoffs
- Validate context preservation in HITL workflows
- Test MD document integration
```

### Logistics Integration Issues
```
Common Issues:
- Export documents not generating
- Customs data incomplete
- Agent handoff failing
- Status sync broken

Resolution Approach:
- Review logistics document generation service
- Check customs data preparation logic
- Validate agent handoff mechanisms
- Test status synchronization
```

## Success Criteria

### Data Collection
- [ ] All 43 cards render with consistent card-based UI
- [ ] Card selection logic works for single and multi-select
- [ ] Validation rules enforce data quality
- [ ] Autofill function provides accurate mock data
- [ ] Data persists correctly through all workflow stages

### Document Generation
- [ ] SOW generates with correct content from card selections
- [ ] All appendices A-F populate accurately
- [ ] Template selection matches order type and complexity
- [ ] Document compilation completes without errors
- [ ] Generated documents are complete and accurate

### Agent Wiring
- [ ] Agents assigned to correct disciplines based on order requirements
- [ ] Capability matching selects appropriate agents
- [ ] Workload balancing distributes tasks efficiently
- [ ] Agent communication passes complete context
- [ ] Agent prompts retrieve and perform correctly

### Context Transfer
- [ ] Order details (Group/Category/Item/Goods) transfer intact
- [ ] Technical specifications maintained across handoffs
- [ ] Compliance requirements accessible to all relevant agents
- [ ] MD docs properly reference and transfer context
- [ ] Context preserved through HITL handoffs

### Logistics Integration
- [ ] Export/import documents generate automatically
- [ ] Customs data complete and accurate for CDC submission
- [ ] Agent handoff from procurement to logistics seamless
- [ ] Status synchronization between disciplines works
- [ ] Audit trail maintained for customs documentation

